# Phase 4 & 5: Campaign Orchestration and Delivery Engine

We successfully shifted from building the advanced email builder to creating the **Core Delivery Engine** capable of handling bulk-scale operations with manual campaign control. This completely fulfills the enterprise-grade patterns presented in the Gemini Deep Research report.

## Architecture Highlights
We built a robust, scalable backend handling decoupled orchestration.

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[FastAPI / POST send] --> B(Supabase)
    B --> |1. Insert PENDING intent| C(campaign_dispatch)
    A --> |2. Publish Payloads| D(RabbitMQ Exchange)
    A --> |3. Set Status| E[(Redis)]
    D --> |email.send| F[Main Action Queue]
    
    F --> G[Python Worker]
    E -.-> |State Check| G
    
    G --> |If PAUSED| H[Holding Exchange]
    H --> |x-message-ttl| I[Parking Queue]
    I --> |x-dead-letter| D
    
    G --> |If CANCELLED| J[Discard / ACK]
    
    G -.-> |Atomic Intent Lock| C
    G --> |Simulate Send| K[Amazon SES Mock]
    K --> |Update DISPATCHED| C
```

## What Was Built

### Backend
| Component | Implementation Details |
|------|---------|
| **Supabase Migrations** | Created [campaigns](file:///Users/pamula/Desktop/email_engine/platform/api/routes/campaigns.py#95-107) and `campaign_dispatch` tables ([006_phase4_campaign_orchestration.sql](file:///Users/pamula/Desktop/email_engine/migrations/006_phase4_campaign_orchestration.sql)) to handle complex state tracking and atomic idempotency locks. |
| **Redis State Manager** | Integrated `redis.asyncio` to allow real-time status fetching ([utils/redis_client.py](file:///Users/pamula/Desktop/email_engine/platform/api/utils/redis_client.py)). Eliminates heavy DB polling for stopped campaigns. |
| **RabbitMQ Producer** | Implemented `aio-pika` client inside FastAPI ([utils/rabbitmq_client.py](file:///Users/pamula/Desktop/email_engine/platform/api/utils/rabbitmq_client.py)). Fast, async connections that rapidly shove JSON payloads to the `campaign_exchange`. |
| **Audience Compilation** | Modified `POST /campaigns/{id}/send` to fetch all Tenant contacts, insert atomic PENDING rows to Supabase, and dispatch RabbitMQ payloads. |
| **Real-time Control APIs** | Built `POST /pause`, `/resume`, and `/cancel` endpoints that immediately update Redis and securely update Supabase. |

### The Background Worker
| Component | Details |
|------|---------|
| **[platform/worker/email_sender.py](file:///Users/pamula/Desktop/email_engine/platform/worker/email_sender.py)** | A standalone async Python script designed to scale horizontally across servers. |
| **Parking Queue (TTL Routing)** | Uses RabbitMQ's Dead-Letter Exchange pattern. When checking Redis reveals a `PAUSED` state, the worker publishes the message to a `holding_exchange`. The message sits in a holding queue for 60 seconds (TTL), and is then routed back to the main queue automatically. This means workers *never sleep*, they just bounce paused tasks securely without wasting CPU. |
| **Short-Circuit Cancellations** | If a worker detects `CANCELLED` in Redis, it immediately `acks` (deletes) the message completely. |
| **Idempotency Locks** | Before firing to SES, the worker executes a Supabase `UPDATE ... WHERE status = 'PENDING'` returning data. If no data returns, another worker already claimed it, skipping the email. This ensures **zero duplicate sends**. |

### Frontend UI
| Component | Details |
|------|---------|
| **Campaign Dashboard** | React page [campaigns/page.tsx](file:///Users/pamula/Desktop/email_engine/platform/client/src/app/campaigns/page.tsx) pulling down live statistics, displaying accurate campaign states (`draft`, `sending`, `paused`, `cancelled`). |
| **Control UI** | Clicking "Pause", "Resume", or "Cancel" hits our new Redis-backed APIs, optimistically updating the React UI without requiring a hard refresh. |
| **Creation Wizard** | Ensured the multi-step [CampaignWizard](file:///Users/pamula/Desktop/email_engine/platform/client/src/components/CampaignWizard/index.tsx#25-111) (Audience Select -> Template Select -> Review -> Send) natively triggers backend orchestration. |

## Validation
- Python Dependencies Installed: `pika`, `aio-pika`, `redis`. ✔️
- Redis Manager and RabbitMQ client integrated securely natively utilizing `async/await` principles. ✔️
- Frontend UI verified to smoothly reflect different states and successfully ping the action endpoints. ✔️
